==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obsequiously
<hw>Ob*se"qui*ous*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an
obsequious manner; compliantly; fawningly.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a manner appropriate to obsequies.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whilst I a while <qex>obsequiously</qex> lament⟦br⟧
The untimely fall of virtuous Lancaster.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obsequiousness</ent>⟦br⟧
